name: Jette Feigenbaum
body:
## Personal

* Born on January 28, 1991
* Can speak Estonian, English, French
* Interested in dogs, tumblr, photography, cooking, blogging and coding
* [Personal website](http://www.jette-feigenbaum.com)
* [My Android apps](https://play.google.com/store/apps/developer?id=Jette)

## Know about
### JavaScript, Ruby on Rails, Git, Heroku, CSS, HTML/HAML, jQuery, Mobile Applications (PhoneGap), WordPress, Backbone.js, Software testing, Website mockups, Photoshop, InDesign, Social Media

## Have worked as
### Project manager in Desk Rock

Feb 2013 - Sept 2013

Desk Rock is an IT company which develops finance software on RoR. I learned Ruby on Rails, Git, Backbone, got to know more about PostgreSQL and a got great overview of how agile IT companies' workflow looks like. I did mostly project leading such as talking to clients and organizing developers’ team work flow, but also got to code a bit and test new features before they went live.

### IT and marketing specialist in Koertekeskus

Jan 2012 - May 2012

Koertekeskus can be translated as “Dog Centre”. As it was a small company, I really did everything from managing the company's website and Facebook profile to writing newsletters and consulting the clients in buying products for their dogs.

## Have studied

### IT systems development in The Estonian Information Technology College

2012-2013

Through IT-college I was introduced to the world of IT and I was shown what can be done with the help of techology and what are the current issues and challenges.

_Had courses like Intro to Java, Web applications etc._

### Ecology in Tartu University

2010-2011

I got a deeper look into how the world works, what kind of living beings are around us, what do they have in common to humans and what things are different. My respect for all living beings on Earth doubled.

_Had courses like Behavior ecology, Zoo-semiotics, Organic chemistry, Genetics, Cell biology, Geology, Evolution, Intro to Zoology_

### Hugo Treffneri Gümnaasium

2007-2010

My class specialised on literature and history. The best thing about highschool was the people. I met very motivated and bright people there, who all had a different outlook to the world and deeper knowledge in some field nobody else knew about.
